Would you like to see how to customize the Facility (e.g., changing it from user to local0) in your Rust setup?




To customize the Facility (e.g., changing it from the default user to local0), you can use the with_extra_fields method in your JournalLog initialization.
The systemd-journal-logger crate does not have a dedicated .with_facility() method, but it allows you to pass any arbitrary systemd field—including SYSLOG_FACILITY—as a global metadata field. 
Updated Rust Code
Add the facility number as an extra field during setup. Note that systemd expects the integer value (e.g., 16 for local0) as a string or byte slice.
rust
use systemd_journal_logger::JournalLog;

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    JournalLog::new()?
        .with_syslog_identifier("umrs-mcs".to_string())
        // SYSLOG_FACILITY: 16 is local0, 17 is local1, etc.
        .with_extra_fields(vec![("SYSLOG_FACILITY", "16")]) 
        .install()?;

    log::set_max_level(log::LevelFilter::Info);
    log::info!("This log is now tagged as local0");

    Ok(())
}


Exactly. Using with_extra_fields is the most efficient way to bake provenance and context into your telemetry without repeating yourself in every single log! call.
Since you are building a system focused on NIST compliance and trust models, this is the "correct" way to ensure every event is stamped with its origin.
Why this is the right approach for your system:
Immutable Provenance: By setting fields like SYSLOG_FACILITY or a custom APP_COMPONENT at initialization, you ensure that even if a developer forgets to add metadata to a specific log::info! call, the record remains compliant and searchable.
Global Searchability: In your umrs.log JSON, every entry will now have these keys. You can use jq to filter the entire log instantly:
bash
# Find only events from a specific facility across the whole log
cat /var/log/umrs.log | jq 'select(.SYSLOG_FACILITY == "16")'
Use code with caution.

Performance: The logger attaches these bytes once and prepends them to the journal socket call, which is faster than formatting a new string for every log line.



Common "Global" Keys for your UMRS project:
Beyond just the facility, you might want to add these to your vec!:
UMRS_SUBSYSTEM: e.g., "ingest", "translator", "validator".
UMRS_TRUST_VERSION: The version of the confidence model currently active.
DEPLOYMENT_ENV: e.g., "dev", "prod", "parallels-vm".
One tiny "gotcha"
Systemd journal keys must be uppercase and contain only alphanumeric characters and underscores (e.g., MY_KEY, not my-key). Your with_extra_fields handles this, but if you pass an invalid key name, systemd might silently drop the field.
